        "en": "<h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>In today's digital age, building apps, websites, and online stores has become essential for any successful business. Whether you're an entrepreneur, a beginner developer, or a merchant looking to expand, understanding how to build these systems will help you make smart and effective decisions.</p>

<h2>1. Define Your Project Goal</h2>
<p>Before coding, ask yourself:</p>
<ul>
  <li>What is the purpose of this website or app? (Showcase products, offer services, direct sales...)</li>
  <li>Who is your target audience?</li>
  <li>What problem does this project solve?</li>
</ul>
<p>Clearly defining the goal makes it easier to choose the right tools and technologies.</p>

<h2>2. Choose the Project Type</h2>
<p>Each type has different requirements:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Website:</strong> Ideal for companies, blogs, or presentation sites.</li>
  <li><strong>Web Application:</strong> Like management systems, accounting tools, or digital platforms.</li>
  <li><strong>Online Store:</strong> For selling products or services online (e.g., Shopify or WooCommerce).</li>
  <li><strong>Mobile App:</strong> Runs on smartphones (iOS & Android), built with React Native or Flutter.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Step-by-Step Development</h2>

<h3>Phase 1: Planning</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Create a site map</li>
  <li>Design user interfaces (UI/UX)</li>
  <li>Define core features (e.g., shopping cart, login, payment)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Phase 2: Choose the Right Tech</h3>
<table border="1" cellpadding="8" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 10px 0;">
  <tr style="background-color:#f2f2f2;">
    <th>Type</th>
    <th>Suggested Tools</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Simple Websites</td>
    <td>HTML, CSS, JavaScript, WordPress</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Web Apps</td>
    <td>React.js, Vue.js, Node.js, Laravel</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Online Stores</td>
    <td>WooCommerce, Shopify, Magento</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Mobile Apps</td>
    <td>React Native, Flutter, Swift, Kotlin</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h3>Phase 3: Development</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Build the frontend (user interface)</li>
  <li>Develop the backend and manage data</li>
  <li>Connect to a database (MySQL or MongoDB)</li>
  <li>Integrate payment gateways (Stripe, PayPal)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Phase 4: Testing</h3>
<p>Before launch, ensure:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Test performance on different devices</li>
  <li>Check loading speed</li>
  <li>Fix security vulnerabilities</li>
  <li>Test the purchase process (for stores)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Phase 5: Launch & Maintenance</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Choose reliable hosting (VPS, AWS, or specialized hosting)</li>
  <li>Buy a professional domain name</li>
  <li>Monitor performance and update regularly</li>
  <li>Add new features based on user feedback</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Tips for Success</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Start with a simple version (MVP), then scale.</li>
  <li>Focus on user experience (UX) more than design.</li>
  <li>Use ready-made tools instead of reinventing the wheel.</li>
  <li>Stay connected with users and collect feedback.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Conclusion</h2>
<p>Building apps, websites, and online stores is no longer limited to experts. With modern tools, anyone can start their digital project. The key is: <strong>good planning, gradual implementation, and continuous improvement</strong>.</p>
<p>Start today, and your first step will lead you to a vast digital world full of opportunities!</p>"
